749
01:02:45,800 --> 01:02:48,640
<i>- Have you missed me?
- Of course I have.</i>

750
01:02:48,880 --> 01:02:51,560
But I'm trying not to be too sad.

751
01:02:51,800 --> 01:02:53,400
Oh, good.

752
01:02:53,640 --> 01:02:55,880
<i>- Brush your teeth.
- I did.</i>

753
01:02:56,120 --> 01:02:57,400
Good boy.

754
01:02:57,640 --> 01:03:01,920
I can't chat all night. There's
a cocktail party for us delegates

755
01:03:02,160 --> 01:03:05,440
down in the ballroom and I'm...

756
01:03:05,680 --> 01:03:06,880
Are you there?

757
01:03:07,120 --> 01:03:10,560
<i>I dropped the phone.
I love you, Bobby!</i>

758
01:03:10,800 --> 01:03:13,440
Don...!

759
01:03:18,400 --> 01:03:21,400
That's funny.

760
01:03:22,600 --> 01:03:25,760
Got cut off.

761
01:03:34,800 --> 01:03:37,720
That 2000...

762
01:03:37,960 --> 01:03:43,120
- It's traveling money, isn't it?
- Yeah, it is.

763
01:03:46,040 --> 01:03:50,240
I lied to you. I didn't tell you
about the lost pet sign I saw.

764
01:03:50,480 --> 01:03:52,920
I know.

765
01:03:53,440 --> 01:03:55,360
When will you leave?

766
01:03:55,600 --> 01:03:57,920
Tomorrow, when your mother gets back.

767
01:03:58,160 --> 01:04:02,040
Collect my winnings from Len Files
at the Corner Pocket

768
01:04:02,280 --> 01:04:04,760
then go.

769
01:04:05,480 --> 01:04:08,800
Will I ever see you again?

770
01:04:09,040 --> 01:04:11,720
No.

771
01:04:11,760 --> 01:04:15,560
And wishing can't make it so.

772
01:04:22,280 --> 01:04:26,040
I don't want you to go.

773
01:04:29,080 --> 01:04:31,520
It's all for the best, kiddo.

774
01:04:31,760 --> 01:04:35,160
It's all for the best.

775
01:04:57,880 --> 01:05:01,800
"In yet another startling
development in Washington

776
01:05:02,040 --> 01:05:06,680
J. Edgar Hoover, the director of
the Federal Bureau of Investigation

777
01:05:06,920 --> 01:05:10,920
today issued a statement denying
the Bureau was involved

778
01:05:11,160 --> 01:05:17,040
in recruiting psychics
in the battle against Communism."

779
01:05:22,400 --> 01:05:27,400
That's really what all this is about,
isn't it, Ted?

780
01:05:32,880 --> 01:05:35,240
Want a root beer?

781
01:05:35,480 --> 01:05:40,760
That's the only good thing about you
going. I can't stand that stuff.

782
01:05:41,000 --> 01:05:43,480
Yeah, I know.

783
01:05:43,720 --> 01:05:47,960
- Do you know everything?
- Nope.

784
01:05:48,480 --> 01:05:51,400
So what happens when you touch people?

785
01:05:51,640 --> 01:05:57,240
I pass on a kind of window
into other people's minds.

786
01:05:57,320 --> 01:06:00,320
Is that why they want you?
This window?

787
01:06:00,560 --> 01:06:04,640
Yeah. I know certain things,
see certain things.

788
01:06:04,880 --> 01:06:08,320
Some see it as a gift,
but to me it's always been a burden.

789
01:06:08,560 --> 01:06:11,400
What I see has a value for some.

790
01:06:11,640 --> 01:06:13,840
Maybe I escaped them this time.

791
01:06:14,080 --> 01:06:16,360
Thanks.

792
01:06:16,600 --> 01:06:18,040
Cheers.

793
01:06:18,280 --> 01:06:21,200
To good health.

794
01:06:22,280 --> 01:06:24,120
Oh, well.

795
01:06:24,360 --> 01:06:27,800
We're all just passing through, kiddo.

796
01:06:28,040 --> 01:06:31,760
Just passing through, that's all.

797
01:06:32,920 --> 01:06:35,640
Tell Carol I'd like to
say goodbye to her.

798
01:06:35,880 --> 01:06:38,400
Sure.

799
01:06:42,600 --> 01:06:46,080
- Hey, Bobby!
- Yeah?

800
01:06:46,120 --> 01:06:50,080
I think you should go find her now.

801
01:06:50,200 --> 01:06:52,920
Okay.

802
01:07:24,280 --> 01:07:26,560
- Hey, Bobby.
- Is Carol home?

803
01:07:26,800 --> 01:07:28,960
No, she went to the ravine
to read

804
01:07:29,200 --> 01:07:32,240
<i>by the tree.</i>

805
01:07:57,000 --> 01:07:59,840
You don't scare me, Bobby Garfield.

806
01:08:00,080 --> 01:08:03,760
If it isn't the Gerber Baby.

807
01:08:06,960 --> 01:08:09,840
No! Please!

808
01:08:10,600 --> 01:08:13,040
Harry?

809
01:08:27,440 --> 01:08:30,800
Carol! Carol!

810
01:08:46,840 --> 01:08:49,960
Is everything okay?

811
01:08:50,200 --> 01:08:53,200
He hit me, Bobby. He hit me hard.

812
01:08:53,440 --> 01:08:55,000
It's okay.

813
01:08:55,240 --> 01:08:57,440
- I'll go get help!
- No, please!

814
01:08:57,680 --> 01:09:00,120
Don't leave me alone.
He might come back.

815
01:09:00,360 --> 01:09:01,400
It'll be okay.

816
01:09:01,640 --> 01:09:03,000
Can you walk?

817
01:09:03,240 --> 01:09:04,120
I don't know.

818
01:09:04,360 --> 01:09:08,600
- Just try, okay?
- Maybe, I don't know.

819
01:09:10,760 --> 01:09:11,840
It'll be okay.

820
01:09:12,080 --> 01:09:16,440
It's okay.
Here, try and stand up, okay?

821
01:09:25,160 --> 01:09:28,320
You have to get on my back, okay?

822
01:09:28,560 --> 01:09:33,480
- Bobby, I can't!
- Yes, you can.

823
01:09:33,720 --> 01:09:34,680
You can.

824
01:09:34,920 --> 01:09:39,760
You have to think about
something else, okay?

825
01:09:39,920 --> 01:09:41,920
Here, get on my back.

826
01:09:42,160 --> 01:09:45,400
Remember at school how we
rode piggyback at recess?

827
01:09:45,640 --> 01:09:49,600
- Yeah.
- This is just like that, okay?

828
01:10:10,880 --> 01:10:15,400
<i>- Bronko Nagurski.
- Nagurski.</i>

829
01:10:21,200 --> 01:10:22,840
<i>Ten yards</i>

830
01:10:23,080 --> 01:10:26,920
<i>seven yards...</i>

831
01:10:30,080 --> 01:10:33,960
<i>Nothing could stop him.</i>

832
01:11:02,800 --> 01:11:05,320
Ted!

833
01:11:06,680 --> 01:11:07,960
Help.

834
01:11:08,200 --> 01:11:09,800
I think her arm's broken.

835
01:11:10,040 --> 01:11:13,600
Come on, Carol. It's all right.

836
01:11:25,800 --> 01:11:28,480
It's all right.

837
01:11:28,520 --> 01:11:29,920
My arm.

838
01:11:30,160 --> 01:11:33,840
Bobby, take her hand, all right?

839
01:11:34,720 --> 01:11:36,920
Oh, yes.

840
01:11:37,160 --> 01:11:40,120
One great, big boy
against one little girl.

841
01:11:40,360 --> 01:11:44,920
He's probably so afraid of you.
Thought you had the heart of a lion.

842
01:11:45,160 --> 01:11:47,080
He hurt me, Ted.

843
01:11:47,320 --> 01:11:49,880
I know. Believe me, I know.

844
01:11:50,120 --> 01:11:54,400
Now listen. I've got to look
at your shoulder. Understand?

845
01:11:54,640 --> 01:11:57,400
I don't want to hurt you.

846
01:11:57,640 --> 01:11:59,520
Oh, my.

847
01:11:59,760 --> 01:12:01,520
He broke my arm.

848
01:12:01,760 --> 01:12:04,600
No, I think it's just dislocated.

849
01:12:04,840 --> 01:12:08,080
And I think I can fix it.

850
01:12:09,080 --> 01:12:11,760
Are you a doctor, Ted?

851
01:12:12,000 --> 01:12:13,840
No, I'm not a doctor.

852
01:12:14,080 --> 01:12:16,520
But as you noted, I'm very strange.

853
01:12:16,760 --> 01:12:18,960
So who knows what I can do?

854
01:12:19,200 --> 01:12:22,920
Do you have the heart of a lion?

855
01:12:24,960 --> 01:12:27,440
Just close your eyes
and try to relax.

856
01:12:27,680 --> 01:12:31,280
Bobby, give me your belt.

857
01:12:31,520 --> 01:12:34,640
Now, Carol, do you know
what pain does?

858
01:12:34,880 --> 01:12:37,800
It rises and travels up the body.

859
01:12:38,040 --> 01:12:39,800
That's it. Thank you.

860
01:12:40,040 --> 01:12:41,600
Listen to me, Carol.

861
01:12:41,840 --> 01:12:43,680
Just listen and relax.

862
01:12:43,920 --> 01:12:46,600
I want you to bite down hard
on the belt.

863
01:12:46,840 --> 01:12:51,800
You're going to bite down
on Bobby's belt and catch the pain.

864
01:12:52,040 --> 01:12:53,640
Now relax.

865
01:12:53,880 --> 01:12:55,480
Close your eyes.

866
01:12:55,720 --> 01:12:57,160
Keep them closed.

867
01:12:57,400 --> 01:13:00,160
You're safe. Just breathe in.

868
01:13:00,400 --> 01:13:03,600
Breathe out. That's it.
There's no pain.

869
01:13:03,840 --> 01:13:07,760
Just listen to my voice.

870
01:13:08,000 --> 01:13:11,320
I can sense them
closing in on me, Bobby.

871
01:13:11,560 --> 01:13:14,720
I know. There's signs everywhere.

872
01:13:14,960 --> 01:13:16,320
Here we go.

873
01:13:16,560 --> 01:13:20,680
Bite down hard and catch... Here we go.

874
01:13:22,920 --> 01:13:24,400
All right.

875
01:13:24,640 --> 01:13:25,560
There.

876
01:13:25,800 --> 01:13:27,480
Ted?

877
01:13:27,720 --> 01:13:30,480
It doesn't hurt anymore.

878
01:13:30,720 --> 01:13:33,360
You do have the heart of a lion.

879
01:13:33,600 --> 01:13:35,280
You did well, kiddo.

880
01:13:35,520 --> 01:13:38,400
What the hell is going on in here?

881
01:13:38,640 --> 01:13:40,440
Mom, what happened to you?

882
01:13:40,680 --> 01:13:45,320
- Take your hands off that little girl!
- Mom, he didn't do anything bad!

883
01:13:45,560 --> 01:13:47,800
How dare you touch her!

884
01:13:48,040 --> 01:13:49,640
He didn't hurt her!

885
01:13:49,880 --> 01:13:52,400
I brought her so Ted could help her!

886
01:13:52,640 --> 01:13:56,280
Go to your room!
And you! You are going to jail!

887
01:13:56,520 --> 01:13:59,920
What happened to you
didn't happen to her.

888
01:14:00,160 --> 01:14:02,920
- Why's her blouse open?
- Her shoulder's hurt!

889
01:14:03,160 --> 01:14:04,840
I said, go to your room!

890
01:14:05,080 --> 01:14:08,520
What Bobby said was true!

891
01:14:09,440 --> 01:14:12,040
Let's clean you up in the bathroom.

892
01:14:12,280 --> 01:14:14,520
He carried me up the hill.

893
01:14:14,760 --> 01:14:16,920
Ted took my pain away.

894
01:14:17,160 --> 01:14:19,360
Don't you touch her!

895
01:14:19,400 --> 01:14:21,520
Go in the bathroom.

896
01:14:21,760 --> 01:14:24,920
I'm calling the police
to tell them everything.

897
01:14:25,160 --> 01:14:28,440
Tell them what happened to you.

898
01:14:28,680 --> 01:14:31,120
You weren't there. You couldn't know.

899
01:14:31,360 --> 01:14:32,760
I know.

900
01:14:33,000 --> 01:14:36,480
I know you didn't realize
the seminar would involve that.

901
01:14:36,720 --> 01:14:42,160
And I know he's growing up
while your mind is on other things.

902
01:14:44,560 --> 01:14:50,760
I'm taking that child home. And you
better not be here when I get back.

903
01:14:56,800 --> 01:14:59,640
- Be careful.
- I'll be fine, don't worry.

904
01:14:59,880 --> 01:15:02,000
Where will you go till it's dark?

905
01:15:02,240 --> 01:15:07,280
The diner near the Corner Pocket,
I guess. Pick up my winnings later.

906
01:15:07,520 --> 01:15:09,960
I want to go with you.

907
01:15:10,200 --> 01:15:12,480
Bobby, come inside, please.

908
01:15:12,720 --> 01:15:15,840
Do as she says, kiddo.

909
01:15:59,200 --> 01:16:01,200
<i>Yes, is this</i>

910
01:16:01,440 --> 01:16:04,840
<i>Housatonic-5837?</i>

911
01:16:05,080 --> 01:16:07,920
Yes, well, I have some information
for you

912
01:16:08,160 --> 01:16:10,840
about Brautigan.

913
01:16:11,080 --> 01:16:14,400
You can find him at
the Corner Pocket tonight

914
01:16:14,640 --> 01:16:16,720
in Bridgeport.

915
01:16:16,960 --> 01:16:19,640
Yes. Now, there's a reward...?

916
01:16:19,880 --> 01:16:20,800
Hello?

917
01:16:21,040 --> 01:16:23,560
Hello...

918
01:16:26,640 --> 01:16:29,800
Bastards.

919
01:17:00,160 --> 01:17:02,160
<i>When your mother writes "bad"</i>

920
01:17:02,400 --> 01:17:07,480
under a mental picture of someone,
she writes it in ink.

921
01:17:08,640 --> 01:17:13,640
I mean, I knew that, but
I didn't think she'd betray me.

922
01:17:17,360 --> 01:17:20,680
See, I need the money to survive

923
01:17:20,920 --> 01:17:24,440
and I can't go back
to the Corner Pocket.

924
01:17:24,680 --> 01:17:27,920
And I need time to think

925
01:17:28,160 --> 01:17:31,400
and there isn't any.

926
01:17:37,720 --> 01:17:40,120
Here's what you do.

927
01:17:40,360 --> 01:17:41,880
Write a note for me.

928
01:17:42,120 --> 01:17:43,720
A note?

929
01:17:43,960 --> 01:17:46,320
Yeah, to the Corner Pocket.

930
01:17:46,560 --> 01:17:49,880
I'll get you your money.

931
01:17:50,240 --> 01:17:53,400
I'm not sure this is a good idea.

932
01:17:53,640 --> 01:17:56,680
Ted, take my hands.

933
01:17:56,720 --> 01:18:02,480
Don't worry. I won't let
the bogeymen get you.

934
01:18:34,280 --> 01:18:37,160
<i>Hello?</i>

935
01:18:38,680 --> 01:18:40,640
<i>Can I help you?</i>

936
01:18:40,880 --> 01:18:44,640
It's about Brautigan.
He took the train. I saw him go.

937
01:18:44,880 --> 01:18:47,160
<i>Stay out of this, kid.</i>

938
01:18:47,400 --> 01:18:51,200
<i>Brautigan's our business.</i>

939
01:18:52,520 --> 01:18:55,760
Don't hurt him.

940
01:18:56,200 --> 01:18:59,400
Please don't hurt him.

941
01:18:59,640 --> 01:19:03,040
<i>Go home, Bobby.</i>

942
01:20:50,640 --> 01:20:54,000
Ted, I got the money!

943
01:21:04,680 --> 01:21:07,640
Ted!

944
01:21:25,400 --> 01:21:27,680
I wouldn't have missed a minute!

945
01:21:27,920 --> 01:21:30,760
Not a single minute!

946
01:21:30,920 --> 01:21:34,680
Not for the whole world!

947
01:21:59,000 --> 01:22:01,520
Where have you been?
I've been worried!

948
01:22:01,760 --> 01:22:03,840
I'm all safe and sound.

949
01:22:04,080 --> 01:22:07,680
Do you have any idea
what you just put me through?

950
01:22:07,920 --> 01:22:12,200
You only think about yourself!

951
01:22:12,440 --> 01:22:13,960
- Bobby...
- Ted's gone.

952
01:22:14,200 --> 01:22:16,880
I'll never see him again.

953
01:22:17,120 --> 01:22:19,960
So you got everything you wanted.
Happy?

954
01:22:20,200 --> 01:22:22,600
There's no money. I don't have a job.

955
01:22:22,840 --> 01:22:26,040
There's plenty of money now!

956
01:22:26,280 --> 01:22:29,360
See how great it worked out,
turning him in?

957
01:22:29,600 --> 01:22:31,840
I did it for you. For your own...

958
01:22:32,080 --> 01:22:36,920
You lie! You always lie.

959
01:22:37,040 --> 01:22:42,360
My father was a good man
and people liked him.

960
01:22:42,440 --> 01:22:45,120
Everyone liked him except you.

961
01:22:45,360 --> 01:22:47,840
You never liked me either.

962
01:22:48,080 --> 01:22:52,960
Then I find a grownup friend
of my own, and you know what?

963
01:22:53,200 --> 01:22:55,960
I loved him.

964
01:22:56,120 --> 01:23:01,640
You didn't just betray him;
you betrayed both of us.

965
01:23:10,480 --> 01:23:12,960
Bobby?

966
01:23:22,160 --> 01:23:23,960
<i>Ted got it right.</i>

967
01:23:24,200 --> 01:23:28,120
<i>It isn't all Atlantis.</i>

968
01:23:28,200 --> 01:23:31,200
<i>My mother got a job outside of Boston.</i>

969
01:23:31,440 --> 01:23:34,760
<i>And I was upset, of course,
but one thing...</i>

970
01:23:35,000 --> 01:23:36,920
<i>I wasn't afraid.</i>

971
01:23:37,160 --> 01:23:40,520
<i>I had Ted to thank for that.</i>

972
01:23:40,760 --> 01:23:43,720
Hey, get out of here.
This is my place now.

973
01:23:43,960 --> 01:23:46,280
You can't. This is everybody's park.

974
01:23:46,520 --> 01:23:49,600
Yes, I can.

975
01:23:51,280 --> 01:23:53,400
Little Bobby Garfield.

976
01:23:53,640 --> 01:23:58,080
Where's your fairy godfather
when you need him?

977
01:24:18,720 --> 01:24:22,640
That was for the Gerber Baby!

978
01:25:12,600 --> 01:25:14,400
Do you need any help?

979
01:25:14,640 --> 01:25:17,520
I'm fine.

980
01:25:35,960 --> 01:25:41,280
Do you think you could ever
see your way to forgiving me?

981
01:25:44,160 --> 01:25:47,960
I'm working on it, Mom.

982
01:26:15,240 --> 01:26:18,600
Carol, we're leaving now.

983
01:26:18,840 --> 01:26:21,720
Oh, no.

984
01:26:21,800 --> 01:26:24,440
Here. It's where I'll be
in Massachusetts.

985
01:26:24,680 --> 01:26:27,560
- Will you write to me?
- Of course.

986
01:26:27,800 --> 01:26:30,160
I'll write to you.

987
01:26:30,400 --> 01:26:33,280
I'll probably be homesick.

988
01:26:33,520 --> 01:26:37,160
I'll never forget you.

989
01:26:41,880 --> 01:26:45,880
Was it you who beat up Harry Doolin?

990
01:26:46,440 --> 01:26:48,400
Good.

991
01:26:48,640 --> 01:26:51,120
Good.

992
01:27:00,160 --> 01:27:03,760
- Carol, wait.
- I can't. Not now.

993
01:27:04,600 --> 01:27:08,720
- But l...
- I love you too, Bobby Garfield.

994
01:27:09,120 --> 01:27:12,760
But I have to go make the salad.

995
01:27:21,120 --> 01:27:23,840
<i>9:35, 25 minutes before 10
on WKMD</i>

996
01:27:24,080 --> 01:27:28,800
<i>serving up the biggest hits
with the Platters.</i>

997
01:27:35,440 --> 01:27:36,960
So, what are we gonna do?

998
01:27:37,200 --> 01:27:42,520
The best we can, Mom.
The best we can.

999
01:27:43,640 --> 01:27:46,000
Well, time and tide wait for no man.

1000
01:27:46,240 --> 01:27:49,120
Ben Jonson called time
"the old bald cheater".

1001
01:27:49,360 --> 01:27:52,160
- Who was Ben Jonson?
- An English writer.

1002
01:27:52,400 --> 01:27:55,680
Foolish about money,
and given to flatulence.

1003
01:27:55,920 --> 01:27:59,080
Flatulence?

1004
01:27:59,120 --> 01:28:02,920
Bobby Garfield!

1005
01:28:30,520 --> 01:28:33,920
Hey!
I don't think you should be in there.

1006
01:28:34,160 --> 01:28:36,160
It's not safe.

1007
01:28:36,400 --> 01:28:40,640
I used to live here when I was a kid.

1008
01:28:43,200 --> 01:28:47,920
- Have you lived here long?
- Only my whole life.

1009
01:28:48,160 --> 01:28:52,480
Oh, wait a minute! Wait, wait, wait.

1010
01:28:54,480 --> 01:28:57,360
Was your mother

1011
01:28:57,760 --> 01:29:00,480
was she...?

1012
01:29:00,720 --> 01:29:04,440
Was she Carol, Carol Gerber?

1013
01:29:04,680 --> 01:29:10,440
- My mom's dead. She died years ago.
- I was sorry to hear that.

1014
01:29:12,040 --> 01:29:16,520
We never kept in touch
like we said we would.

1015
01:29:19,360 --> 01:29:21,560
My God.

1016
01:29:21,800 --> 01:29:25,240
You're the boy on the Ferris wheel?

1017
01:29:25,480 --> 01:29:31,840
- Mom told me about that.
- She promised she'd never tell anyone.

1018
01:29:32,080 --> 01:29:36,360
She said you were beautiful.

1019
01:29:38,280 --> 01:29:41,360
One of us was.

1020
01:30:13,720 --> 01:30:18,080
You can keep that, if you want.

1021
01:30:19,680 --> 01:30:22,440
I'm Bobby.

1022
01:30:22,800 --> 01:30:27,360
- Molly.
- Molly.

1023
01:30:31,440 --> 01:30:35,520
She had the heart of a lion.

1024
01:31:13,880 --> 01:31:17,240
<i>I never heard from
Ted Brautigan again.</i>

1025
01:31:17,480 --> 01:31:21,520
<i>Not that I didn't think of him.
I always have</i>

1026
01:31:21,760 --> 01:31:24,800
<i>and always will.</i>

1027
01:31:25,160 --> 01:31:30,880
<i>Because that summer was the last
of my childhood.</i>

1028
01:31:31,120 --> 01:31:35,280
<i>And though I never again saw
what people were thinking</i>

1029
01:31:35,520 --> 01:31:40,280
<i>there was an enduring gift
that he left me.</i>

1030
01:31:40,520 --> 01:31:45,280
<i>What Ted did was open my eyes</i>

1031
01:31:45,520 --> 01:31:49,240
<i>and let the future in.</i>

1032
01:31:50,040 --> 01:31:53,760
<i>I wouldn't have missed a minute of it.</i>

1033
01:31:54,000 --> 01:31:57,400
<i>Not for all the world.</i>

